.TH MD-VIEWER 1 "March 2026" "MD Viewer" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
md-viewer \- Markdown file viewer with live reload
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mdv
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIFILE\fR
.br
.B mdv-admin
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B bun run dev
.RI [SERVER\ OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
MD Viewer is a lightweight Markdown file viewer that provides live preview
with automatic reload when files change. It consists of a server component
that serves the web interface and CLI tools for adding files and managing data.
.SH CLI COMMANDS
.SS mdv (Client)
.TP
.B mdv \fIFILE\fR
Add a Markdown file to the viewer. By default, the file will be added and
switched to. Supports both local file paths and remote URLs (http/https).
.SS mdv-admin (Administration)
.TP
.B mdv-admin stats
Display statistics about sync records (total files, expired records, recent parents).
Works with or without running server.
.TP
.B mdv-admin cleanup
Clean up expired sync records (older than 6 months).
Works with or without running server.
.SH CLI OPTIONS
.SS mdv Options
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
Specify the server port (default: 3000)
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Specify the server host (default: localhost)
.TP
.B \-\-no\-focus
Add the file without switching to it. By default, the viewer will switch
to the newly added file.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Display help information and exit
.SS mdv-admin Options
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
Specify the server port (default: 3000)
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Specify the server host (default: localhost)
.TP
.B \-\-help
Display help information and exit
.SH SERVER OPTIONS
The server can be configured using environment variables:
.TP
.B PORT
Server port number (default: 3000)
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using mdv (Client)
.TP
Add a local file and switch to it:
.B mdv README.md
.TP
Add a file without switching:
.B mdv \-\-no\-focus notes.md
.TP
Add a file using a specific server port:
.B mdv \-p 3001 README.md
.TP
Add a remote Markdown file:
.B mdv https://example.com/doc.md
.SS Using mdv-admin (Administration)
.TP
View sync statistics:
.B mdv-admin stats
.TP
Clean up expired records:
.B mdv-admin cleanup
.TP
Check stats on custom port:
.B mdv-admin stats \-p 3001
.SS Starting the Server
.TP
Start the server on default port:
.B bun run dev
.TP
Start the server on a custom port:
.B PORT=8080 bun run dev
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/md-viewer/config.json
User configuration file. See
.BR md-viewer.config (5)
for details.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/md-viewer/
Application data directory
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PORT
Server listening port (default: 3000)
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR md-viewer.config (5)
